People don't play sports because its fun. Ask any athlete, most of them hate it, but they couldn't imagine their life without it. It's part of them, the love/hate relationship. It's what they live for. They live for the practices, parties, cheers, long bus rides, invitationals, countless pairs of different types of shoes, water, Gatorade, & coaches you hate but appreciate. They live for the way it feels when they beat the other team, and knowing those two extra sprints they ran in practice were worth it. They live for the way they become a family with their team, they live for the countless songs they sing in their head while training all those hours. They live for the competition, they live for the friends, the practices, the memories, the pain, its who they are. It's who we are. -John Bruenning

To anyone who reads this: I think we lost the ABBQ game because our top players were tired. Tired in the 7th game of the weekend each playing to 15. If you want to improve your endurance, you can't ONLY do sprints for your conditioning. When was the last time you put on running shoes and ran for 15-20 minutes? Biking and swimming don't help improve your bodies oxygen utilization or endurance because the sport specific muscles will only intelligently metabolize for energy efficiently if you train based off running and the necessary biomechanics with your muscles. 

Also, ice less frequently and instead increase the time spent messaging and compressing sore muscles.

2012264.description:
Good Story below

Getting CPrawr certified today

Davis Pod.

After pod I felt like running more. I put on my ankle weights and ran hard for 12-15 minutes. I pushed myself really hard for the last 4-5 minutes having already placed a finish line in my head. When I crossed that line, I was sweaty, gasping for air, and exhausted. As I walked around regaining consciousness, I witnessed a college aged girl pull horizontally onto a one-way street, and then slowly back up onto a clearly red marked sidewalk. She ended up hitting the car behind her whom was actually in a parking space. When she got out of the car, I lite her up. "WHAT THE FUCK ARE YOU DOING. DON"T YOU KNOW HOW TO FUCKING DRIVE YOU GODDAMN IDIOT!!!! YOU'RE NOT EVEN IN A PARKING SPACE". It was the greatest feeling ever after running to just rip into a shitty driver like that. Cool story huh.
AJ Cone Drill, stretching, trying to salvage my back
